nullis: so most recent editors with most MSS including the best. Or. and Tr. read non ullis ; many early editions non illis-3 two early editions and Mo. nonnullis. nullis, nan ullis, and non nullis differ very little in MSS, since non was repre- sented by the compendium n'. But nullis, substantively used, 15 very rare, while non ullis and nonnullis, though unsuitable in meaning here, are fairly common. It is therefore more probable that the copyists of inferior MSS mistook nullis for ἦ ullis = non ullis than that the earesul copyists of RVG Gr B, etc. omitted the top stroke and changed ἦ ullis into nullis, thereby introducing a rare use of the word.
